d flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.0,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"good","read":"Conservatively financed (D/E 0.00\u00d7, interest cover 71.8\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":10.04,"unit":"% YoY","status":"ok","read":"Profit up 10% YoY \u2014 modest.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":11.9,"pe_percentile":36.0,"median_pe":15.2,"earnings_yield_pct":8.4,"pb":3.2,"ev_ebitda":8.72,"quality_score":58.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":34.9,"peg":0.34,"cheapness":{"status":"ok","read":"P/E at the 36-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 mid-range vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 11.9\u00d7 earnings for ~35% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22480.34\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining o